  "text": "In this study, we analyzed a 96-gene set to improve prognostic prediction in glioma, notably when based on IDH and 1p19q status. Since radiotherapy can modify gene expression [CITATION_1] , we only analyzed the glioma samples resected from patients who had not undergone radiotherapy and/or chemotherapy. A 26-gene signature identified two molecular subgroups that were significantly correlated with patient survival and validated on an independent TCGA cohort.",
